From Clingmans Dome Parking Area follow paved trail towards the lookout tower.  Past the visitor center about 0.2 mile  there is a concrete bench on the right side of the trail.  This bench is the first reference point to a Red Spruce with a diameter of 21.2 cm.  It is about 50 meters at 20 degrees from the bench..  The next tree is a Red Spruce with a diameter of 50.2 cm at 25 degrees.  This Spruce is on the ridge.  The next Spruce is about 30 meters at 38 degrees with a diameter of 23 cm. From this tree the top right corner of the hectare ATBI Plot is 55 degrees at about 25 meters.  This corner is marked with a thin red electric fence post about 3 feet tall.  All tree tags are marked "ATBI".  The hectare is marked off with nylon string around the parameter.  The Long Term Monitoring Plot is also marked with string.  Do not disturb the Long Term Monitoring Plot.

column_contents: From Clingmans Dome Parking Area follow paved trail towards the lookout tower.  Past the visitor center about 0.2 mile  there is a concrete bench on the right side of the trail.  This bench is the first reference point to a Red Spruce with a diameter of 21.2 cm.  It is about 50 meters at 20 degrees from the bench..  The next tree is a Red Spruce with a diameter of 50.2 cm at 25 degrees.  This Spruce is on the ridge.  The next Spruce is about 30 meters at 38 degrees with a diameter of 23 cm. From this tree the top right corner of the hectare ATBI Plot is 55 degrees at about 25 meters.  This corner is marked with a thin red electric fence post about 3 feet tall.  All tree tags are marked "ATBI".  The hectare is marked off with nylon string around the parameter.  The Long Term Monitoring Plot is also marked with string.  Do not disturb the Long Term Monitoring Plot.
Not rooted in plot but is overhanging
species occurred in rest of plot; aggregate of modules 1, 4, 5, 6, 7, and 10

column_contents: From Clingmans Dome Parking Area follow paved trail towards the lookout tower.  Past the visitor center about 0.2 mile  there is a concrete bench on the right side of the trail.  This bench is the first reference point to a Red Spruce with a diameter of 21.2 cm.  It is about 50 meters at 20 degrees from the bench..  The next tree is a Red Spruce with a diameter of 50.2 cm at 25 degrees.  This Spruce is on the ridge.  The next Spruce is about 30 meters at 38 degrees with a diameter of 23 cm. From this tree the top right corner of the hectare ATBI Plot is 55 degrees at about 25 meters.  This corner is marked with a thin red electric fence post about 3 feet tall.  All tree tags are marked "ATBI".  The hectare is marked off with nylon string around the parameter.  The Long Term Monitoring Plot is also marked with string.  Do not disturb the Long Term Monitoring Plot.
along trail to Clingmans Dome lookout tower
Not rooted in plot but is overhanging
species occurred in rest of plot; aggregate of modules 1, 4, 5, 6, 7, and 10

column_contents: along trail to Clingmans Dome lookout tower

From Clingmans Dome Parking Area follow paved trail towards the lookout tower.  Past the visitor center about 0.2 mile  there is a concrete bench on the right side of the trail.  This bench is the first reference point to a Red Spruce with a diameter of 21.2 cm.  It is about 50 meters at 20 degrees from the bench..  The next tree is a Red Spruce with a diameter of 50.2 cm at 25 degrees.  This Spruce is on the ridge.  The next Spruce is about 30 meters at 38 degrees with a diameter of 23 cm. From this tree the top right corner of the hectare ATBI Plot is 55 degrees at about 25 meters.  This corner is marked with a thin red electric fence post about 3 feet tall.  All tree tags are marked "ATBI".  The hectare is marked off with nylon string around the parameter.  The Long Term Monitoring Plot is also marked with string.  Do not disturb the Long Term Monitoring Plot.

From Clingmans Dome Parking Area follow paved trail towards the lookout tower.  Past the visitor center about 0.2 mile  there is a concrete bench on the right side of the trail.  This bench is the first reference point to a Red Spruce with a diameter of 21.2 cm.  It is about 50 meters at 20 degrees from the bench..  The next tree is a Red Spruce with a diameter of 50.2 cm at 25 degrees.  This Spruce is on the ridge.  The next Spruce is about 30 meters at 38 degrees with a diameter of 23 cm. From this tree the top right corner of the hectare ATBI Plot is 55 degrees at about 25 meters.  This corner is marked with a thin red electric fence post about 3 feet tall.  All tree tags are marked "ATBI".  The hectare is marked off with nylon string around the parameter.  The Long Term Monitoring Plot is also marked with string.  Do not disturb the Long Term Monitoring Plot.
along trail to Clingmans Dome lookout tower

column_contents: along trail to Clingmans Dome lookout tower

From Clingmans Dome Parking Area follow paved trail towards the lookout tower.  Past the visitor center about 0.2 mile  there is a concrete bench on the right side of the trail.  This bench is the first reference point to a Red Spruce with a diameter of 21.2 cm.  It is about 50 meters at 20 degrees from the bench..  The next tree is a Red Spruce with a diameter of 50.2 cm at 25 degrees.  This Spruce is on the ridge.  The next Spruce is about 30 meters at 38 degrees with a diameter of 23 cm. From this tree the top right corner of the hectare ATBI Plot is 55 degrees at about 25 meters.  This corner is marked with a thin red electric fence post about 3 feet tall.  All tree tags are marked "ATBI".  The hectare is marked off with nylon string around the parameter.  The Long Term Monitoring Plot is also marked with string.  Do not disturb the Long Term Monitoring Plot.

column_contents: From Clingmans Dome Parking Area follow paved trail towards the lookout tower.  Past the visitor center about 0.2 mile  there is a concrete bench on the right side of the trail.  This bench is the first reference point to a Red Spruce with a diameter of 21.2 cm.  It is about 50 meters at 20 degrees from the bench..  The next tree is a Red Spruce with a diameter of 50.2 cm at 25 degrees.  This Spruce is on the ridge.  The next Spruce is about 30 meters at 38 degrees with a diameter of 23 cm. From this tree the top right corner of the hectare ATBI Plot is 55 degrees at about 25 meters.  This corner is marked with a thin red electric fence post about 3 feet tall.  All tree tags are marked "ATBI".  The hectare is marked off with nylon string around the parameter.  The Long Term Monitoring Plot is also marked with string.  Do not disturb the Long Term Monitoring Plot.

column_contents: along trail to Clingmans Dome lookout tower

From Clingmans Dome Parking Area follow paved trail towards the lookout tower.  Past the visitor center about 0.2 mile  there is a concrete bench on the right side of the trail.  This bench is the first reference point to a Red Spruce with a diameter of 21.2 cm.  It is about 50 meters at 20 degrees from the bench..  The next tree is a Red Spruce with a diameter of 50.2 cm at 25 degrees.  This Spruce is on the ridge.  The next Spruce is about 30 meters at 38 degrees with a diameter of 23 cm. From this tree the top right corner of the hectare ATBI Plot is 55 degrees at about 25 meters.  This corner is marked with a thin red electric fence post about 3 feet tall.  All tree tags are marked "ATBI".  The hectare is marked off with nylon string around the parameter.  The Long Term Monitoring Plot is also marked with string.  Do not disturb the Long Term Monitoring Plot.
STATUS: Native, Abundant, Present in Park; POLICY: FSC, SR-L/T;
STATUS: Native, Rare, Present in Park;

Overhanging, but not rooted in module
along trail to Clingmans Dome lookout tower

From Clingmans Dome Parking Area follow paved trail towards the lookout tower.  Past the visitor center about 0.2 mile  there is a concrete bench on the right side of the trail.  This bench is the first reference point to a Red Spruce with a diameter of 21.2 cm.  It is about 50 meters at 20 degrees from the bench..  The next tree is a Red Spruce with a diameter of 50.2 cm at 25 degrees.  This Spruce is on the ridge.  The next Spruce is about 30 meters at 38 degrees with a diameter of 23 cm. From this tree the top right corner of the hectare ATBI Plot is 55 degrees at about 25 meters.  This corner is marked with a thin red electric fence post about 3 feet tall.  All tree tags are marked "ATBI".  The hectare is marked off with nylon string around the parameter.  The Long Term Monitoring Plot is also marked with string.  Do not disturb the Long Term Monitoring Plot.

column_contents: along trail to Clingmans Dome lookout tower

From Clingmans Dome Parking Area follow paved trail towards the lookout tower.  Past the visitor center about 0.2 mile  there is a concrete bench on the right side of the trail.  This bench is the first reference point to a Red Spruce with a diameter of 21.2 cm.  It is about 50 meters at 20 degrees from the bench..  The next tree is a Red Spruce with a diameter of 50.2 cm at 25 degrees.  This Spruce is on the ridge.  The next Spruce is about 30 meters at 38 degrees with a diameter of 23 cm. From this tree the top right corner of the hectare ATBI Plot is 55 degrees at about 25 meters.  This corner is marked with a thin red electric fence post about 3 feet tall.  All tree tags are marked "ATBI".  The hectare is marked off with nylon string around the parameter.  The Long Term Monitoring Plot is also marked with string.  Do not disturb the Long Term Monitoring Plot.
STATUS: Native, Abundant, Present in Park; POLICY: FSC, SR-L/T;
STATUS: Native, Rare, Present in Park;

along trail to Clingmans Dome lookout tower

From Clingmans Dome Parking Area follow paved trail towards the lookout tower.  Past the visitor center about 0.2 mile  there is a concrete bench on the right side of the trail.  This bench is the first reference point to a Red Spruce with a diameter of 21.2 cm.  It is about 50 meters at 20 degrees from the bench..  The next tree is a Red Spruce with a diameter of 50.2 cm at 25 degrees.  This Spruce is on the ridge.  The next Spruce is about 30 meters at 38 degrees with a diameter of 23 cm. From this tree the top right corner of the hectare ATBI Plot is 55 degrees at about 25 meters.  This corner is marked with a thin red electric fence post about 3 feet tall.  All tree tags are marked "ATBI".  The hectare is marked off with nylon string around the parameter.  The Long Term Monitoring Plot is also marked with string.  Do not disturb the Long Term Monitoring Plot.

question: For each vehicle, show the road speed limit, the highest speed the vehicle was recorded by the event data recorder, and how much higher or lower than the speed limit the vehicle was traveling. Limit travel speed and speedlimit to values less than 300 kph.
text: For each vehicle, show the road speed limit, the highest speed the vehicle was recorded by the event data recorder, and how much higher or lower than the speed limit the vehicle was traveling. Limit travel speed and speedlimit to values less than 300 kph.
sql: SELECT SPEEDLIMIT, MAXSPEED, MAXSPEED - SPEEDLIMIT DIFF FROM GV JOIN ( 	SELECT CASEID, VEHNO, MAX(PVALUE) MAXSPEED FROM EDRPRECRASH 	WHERE PCODE = 1010 AND PVALUE < 300 	GROUP BY CASEID, VEHNO ) S ON GV.CASEID = S.CASEID AND GV.VEHNO = S.VEHNO WHERE SPEEDLIMIT < 300

question: Which vehicle make with more than 5 vehicles in the database has the highest number of distracted drivers in proportion to the total number of the make and model in the data?
text: Which vehicle make with more than 5 vehicles in the database has the highest number of distracted drivers in proportion to the total number of the make and model in the data?
sql: SELECT MAKE, COUNT(*) AS VEHICLE_COUNT, COUNT(DISTRACTN) AS DISTRACT_COUNT, 	CAST(COUNT(DISTRACTN) AS FLOAT) / CAST(COUNT(*) AS FLOAT) AS PROP_DISTRACT FROM VPICDECODE V LEFT JOIN DISTRACT D ON V.CASEID = D.CASEID AND V.VEHNO = D.VEHNO GROUP BY MAKE HAVING COUNT(*) > 5 ORDER BY PROP_DISTRACT DESC

question: List the number of crashes by vehicle make from most to least. Show how many of these crashes resulted in a fire. Calculate the proportion of total crashes by make to crashes with a fire

Moving forward bird surveys on Maui will be in cooperation with partners, so need to have all the bird data together in the database.  Non-NPS data will not be released to the public.

column_contents: 411 2017 HALE detection records were updated to Chlorodrepanis virens wilsoni.
Imported the 2017 non-HALE Maui Forest Bird Recovery Project stations and data into the database.

The wrong subspecies of Amakihi was entered for 2017 HALE Amakihi detections.Chlorodrepanis virens virens was entered for 2017 HALE bird detections when the correct subspecies is Chlorodrepanis virens wilsoni.
Moving forward bird surveys on Maui will be in cooperation with partners, so need to have all the bird data together in the database.  Non-NPS data will not be released to the public.

question: What percent of stations has the bird with the common name Hawaii Amakihi been observed at?
text: What percent of stations has the bird with the common name Hawaii Amakihi been observed at?
sql: select 100 * (sum(sighted) / count(distinct station_id)) as perc_stations from ( 	select distinct tbl_stations.station_id, case  			when tlu_species.common_name = 'Hawaii Amakihi' then 1.0 else 0.0 			end as sighted 	from tbl_stations 	join tbl_events on tbl_stations.station_id = tbl_events.station_id 	join tbl_observations on tbl_observations.event_id = tbl_events.event_id 	join tlu_species on tlu_species.species_id = tbl_observations.species_id ) sightings

question: What is the average canopy height of each species' habitats? Include the common name and scientfic name of each species. Ensure the average has decimal precision.

The Customer Receivables Aging dashboard provides an analysis of a company's accounts receivables and key accounts status. It shows the percentage distribution of overdue receivables and future remit, an historical trend of aging amounts, forecasted remit amounts, and the breakdown of these amounts for the top five customers or sales employees.

column_contents: The Service Call Status dashboard provides different views of service calls being handled by service employees: new service calls for the current date, the trend of service calls, and any calls due today or overdue calls. For each service queue, the dashboard shows employees' workload and service call turnover.

The Customer Receivables Aging dashboard provides an analysis of a company's accounts receivables and key accounts status. It shows the percentage distribution of overdue receivables and future remit, an historical trend of aging amounts, forecasted remit amounts, and the breakdown of these amounts for the top five customers or sales employees.
